The optical properties of the synthesized pristine and N doped TiO2 nanotubes were analyzed using UV-visible Diffuse Reflectance Spectroscopy (DRS) (Fig. 5). The Kubelka-Munk (KM) function corresponding to the DRS spectra is denoted as4F(K)=(αhv)1/n=A(hv−Eg)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
